{"title":"Children's social care providers: fees and inspection frequency","public_updated_at":"2017-02-20T10:02:13Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>We’re seeking views on the following proposed changes to <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2015/551/made\">Her Majesty’s Chief Inspector of Education, Children’s Services and Skills (Fees and Frequency of Inspections) (Children’s Homes etc.) Regulations 2015</a>, with a view to regulations coming into force in April 2017:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a 10% increase on current fees for most settings where fees are not already at full cost recovery</li>\n  <li>amending the frequency of Ofsted inspections for those registered children’s homes which currently have an overall effectiveness judgement of ‘good’ or ‘outstanding’</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The consultation will run for 5 weeks and takes account of the Christmas holiday that falls within the consultation period.</p>\n\n</div>","closing_date":"2017-01-17T23:45:00.000+00:00","emphasised_organisations":["ebd15ade-73b2-4eaf-b1c3-43034a42eb37"],"opening_date":"2016-12-13T14:00:00.000+00:00","change_history":[{"public_timestamp":"2017-02-20T10:02:13.000+00:00","note":"Added government response."},{"public_timestamp":"2016-12-13T14:00:00.000+00:00","note":"First published."}],"held_on_another_website_url":"https://consult.education.gov.uk/children-in-care/fees-and-frequency-of-inspection-regulations","final_outcome_detail":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>Summary of the responses we received, along with the government’s response outlining the next steps.</p>\n</div>","final_outcome_documents":["<section class=\"attachment embedded\" id=\"attachment_1962688\">\n  <div class=\"attachment-thumb\">\n      <a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"thumbnail\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/592275/Consultation_Response_16.02.17.pdf\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/592275/thumbnail_Consultati